
Classic Children’s Stories
The Little Prince by Antoine de Saint-Exupéry
A magical tale of a young prince exploring different planets, teaching profound lessons about love, loss, and friendship.

Alice’s Adventures in Wonderland by Lewis Carroll
Alice falls into a fantastical world of talking animals, mad tea parties, and quirky characters like the Cheshire Cat and Mad Hatter.

Peter Pan by J.M. Barrie
The story of a boy who refuses to grow up and his adventures in Neverland with Wendy, Captain Hook, and the Lost Boys.

The Wind in the Willows by Kenneth Grahame
A heartwarming tale of animal friends like Mole, Ratty, Badger, and the adventurous Mr. Toad.

The Velveteen Rabbit by Margery Williams
A touching story about a toy rabbit's wish to become real, highlighting the power of love and belief.

Modern Children’s Stories
Harry Potter Series by J.K. Rowling
Follow Harry and his friends as they navigate the magical world of Hogwarts and fight against the dark wizard Voldemort.

The Gruffalo by Julia Donaldson
A clever mouse invents a fearsome creature called the Gruffalo, only to discover it might be real after all!

Diary of a Wimpy Kid by Jeff Kinney
A hilarious series about middle school life, written in the form of a diary by Greg Heffley.

Matilda by Roald Dahl
A gifted girl with telekinetic powers stands up to her cruel parents and the terrifying headmistress Miss Trunchbull.

The Magic Tree House Series by Mary Pope Osborne
Siblings Jack and Annie go on time-traveling adventures using a magical treehouse.

